India Adds Record Power-Generation Capacity, Coal Watch Says

-- B y   D i n a k a r   S e t h u r a m a n
-- 
2011-04-06T05:59:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/india-adds-record-power-generation-capacity-coal-watch-says.html
India added record power capacity in
the year ended March 2011,  India Coal Market Watch  said, citing
Power Minister Sushil Kumar Shinde.  The country expanded production capacity by 15,795
megawatts, led by NTPC Ltd., Adani Power Ltd., Reliance Power
Ltd. and Tata Power Co., the industry newsletter said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dinakar Sethuraman in  Singapore  at 
 dinakar@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Clyde Russell at   crussell7@bloomberg.net . 